name: Ash Way Park and Ride WALK IN Covid Vaccine Clinic
address: Ash Way Park & Ride WALK IN: 16327 Ash Way, Lynnwood WA, 98087
info:
**THIS IS A 2ND DOSE PFIZER CLINIC ONLY**
Starting May 13, 2021, everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, you must be 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine. Any minors receiving the vaccine will need a parent or guardian *physically present* to sign the consent form. 

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info: This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. This is a walk in clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 daily from 12pm until mall closing. We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Care-A-Van From My Heart to Yours
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose, Pfizer 1st/2nd dose Clinic and is by appointment or walk in.  Please note: Pfizer has been authorized for ages 12 – 17 with parental authorization. Johnson & Johnson is authorized for patients over the age of 18. This is a walk-up location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill.  It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are still required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
info: ***1ST DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA DOSIS PFIZER!!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at the Yakima Greenway at booth #36, which is right next to the French Merci Train (railcar) located at Sarg Hubbard Park. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live in and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. La clínica de vacunación se llevará a cabo en Yakima Greenway en el espacio # 36, que está al lado del French Merci Train (vagón) ubicado en Sarg Hubbard Park. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 12 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
